OL,3,CGovernment must 'revise' plan for Post
OL,4,COffice compensation, MPs say
OL,6,F"People who were, over years and
OL,7,Fyears, disbelieved, bankrupt,
OL,8,Fcriminalised, sent to prison, had
OL,9,Ftheir lives completely upended for
OL,10,Fwrongs that they did not commit, have
OL,11,Fexperienced something akin to a second
OL,12,Ftrial as they sought to clear their
OL,13,Fnames and receive redress.
OL,15,F"The government's response to our
OL,16,Frecommendations is a start. But we
OL,17,Frespectfully ask ministers to listen
OL,18,Fharder to what the Committee has
OL,19,Frecommended, reflect again on what we
OL,20,Fproposed and re-submit its response to
OL,21,Fthe Committee.
